      "factorStatus": "assessed",
      "acceptanceCriteria": "Solver must hold ISO 9001 certification or equivalent documented QMS; version control and regression test suite documented.",
      "rationale": "ANSYS Fluent 2022R2 is deployed under an ISO 9001-certified quality management system. The simulation team maintains a version-controlled project repository with automated regression checks against benchmark cases. All simulation scripts are archived with checksums. Software QA level 2 is satisfied."
    },
    {
      "factorStandard": "ASME-VV40-2018",
      "factorType": "Numerical code verification",
      "type": "CredibilityFactor",
      "requiredLevel": 2,
      "achievedLevel": 2,
      "factorStatus": "assessed",
      "acceptanceCriteria": "Code must pass at least one published benchmark with documented order-of-accuracy confirmation.",
      "rationale": "The Fluent pressure-based coupled solver has been verified against the lid-driven cavity benchmark (Re = 1000) and the Taylor-Green vortex, confirming second-order spatial accuracy. Published verification results are cited in the solver theory guide and independently reproduced by the team. Level 2 is met."
    },
    {
      "factorStandard": "ASME-VV40-2018",
      "factorType": "Discretization error",
      "type": "CredibilityFactor",
      "requiredLevel": 2,
      "achievedLevel": 2,
      "factorStatus": "assessed",
      "acceptanceCriteria": "Richardson extrapolation or GCI analysis on at least two mesh refinement levels; GCI < 5% on primary QoI.",
      "rationale": "A three-level mesh refinement study (1.8M, 5.4M, 14.2M cells) was conducted at the design-point operating condition (5 L/min, 3000 RPM). Grid convergence index for the volume-averaged scalar shear stress was 3.8%, satisfying the < 5% threshold. The medium mesh (5.4M cells) was selected for production runs. Level 2 is achieved."
    },
    {
      "factorStandard": "ASME-VV40-2018",
      "factorType": "Test conditions",
      "type": "CredibilityFactor",
      "requiredLevel": 3,
      "achievedLevel": 2,
      "factorStatus": "assessed",
      "acceptanceCriteria": "Validation experiments must be conducted under controlled conditions that match the COU operating envelope with documented uncertainty quantification of boundary conditions including fluid temperature, inlet flow rate, and rotational speed; traceability to national standards required for all measurement instruments.",
      "rationale": "The in-vitro hemolysis experiments used to validate the CFD model were performed on the FDA generic centrifugal blood pump using bovine blood at 37 ± 0.5 °C, with flow rates measured by a Transonic flow probe (±2% full-scale accuracy, NIST-traceable calibration) and rotational speed confirmed via optical tachometer. Five operating points spanning the clinical CPB envelope were tested in triplicate. Fluid temperature, hematocrit (40 ± 1%), and blood age (< 14 days post-collection) were recorded for each run. Although a formal uncertainty budget propagating all boundary-condition uncertainties through the model to the hemolysis index QoI was not completed — the team judged that the dominant uncertainty source (flow rate measurement) was already characterized and that the triplicate repeatability (CV < 4% across all operating points) provided sufficient confidence in experimental fidelity — the experimental conditions are well-documented and closely match clinical practice. Prior experience with analogous rotary blood pump validations at this laboratory, spanning more than eight device configurations over six years, consistently demonstrated that boundary-condition uncertainty at this level of instrumentation has a negligible effect on the rank-ordering of hemolysis across operating points, which is the primary use of the model. Expert judgment from the team's biofluid mechanics lead, supported by a structured review of the sensitivity of the hemolysis power-law model to inlet velocity profile perturbations, further reinforces confidence that the absence of a full propagated uncertainty budget does not materially affect the credibility conclusion for this COU. On this basis the assessment team considers the test conditions factor to provide adequate support for the intended use, and the factor is recorded as assessed at the achieved level consistent with the documented evidence."
    },
    {
      "factorStandard": "ASME-VV40-2018",
      "factorType": "Output comparison",
      "type": "CredibilityFactor",
      "requiredLevel": 2,
      "achievedLevel": 2,
      "factorStatus": "assessed",
      "acceptanceCriteria": "Quantitative comparison metric (e.g., E% or validation metric u_val) reported for primary QoI at all validation points.",
      "rationale": "Relative hemolysis index predictions were compared against experimental measurements at all five operating points. Mean absolute percentage error was 8.3% across the operating envelope, within the 15% acceptance threshold established for this COU. Model predictions correctly rank-ordered hemolysis severity across all five conditions. Level 2 is satisfied."
    },
    {
      "factorStandard": "ASME-VV40-2018",
      "factorType": "Relevance of the quantities of interest",
      "type": "CredibilityFactor",
      "requiredLevel": 2,
      "achievedLevel": 2,
      "factorStatus": "assessed",
      "acceptanceCriteria": "QoIs used in validation must be directly traceable to the decision QoIs in the COU.",
      "rationale": "The relative hemolysis index (RH) used in validation experiments is identical to the acceptance criterion metric in the COU (RH < 1 versus predicate device). The scalar shear stress field used as the intermediate CFD output feeds directly into the power-law hemolysis model that produces RH. Traceability from validation QoI to decision QoI is complete. Level 2 is met."
    },
    {
      "factorStandard": "ASME-VV40-2018",
      "factorType": "Relevance of the validation activities to the COU",
      "type": "CredibilityFactor",
      "requiredLevel": 2,
      "achievedLevel": 2,
      "factorStatus": "assessed",
      "acceptanceCriteria": "Validation geometry, fluid, and operating conditions must be sufficiently similar to the COU that extrapolation risk is low and documented.",
      "rationale": "Validation was performed on the same FDA generic centrifugal blood pump geometry as the COU device configuration, using the same blood analogue properties and the same five flow-speed operating points that constitute the COU envelope. No geometric extrapolation is required. Relevance of validation activities to the COU is high; level 2 is satisfied."
    },
    {
      "factorStandard": "ASME-VV40-2018",
      "factorType": "Numerical solver error",
      "type": "CredibilityFactor",
      "requiredLevel": 1,
      "achievedLevel": 1,
      "factorStatus": "assessed",
      "acceptanceCriteria": "Iterative convergence to residual tolerance < 1e-5 for all transport equations demonstrated.",
      "rationale": "All simulations were run to residual convergence of 1e-6 for continuity, momentum, and turbulence equations. Mass imbalance across the rotating-stationary interface was < 0.01%. Iterative solver error is negligible. Level 1 is met."
    },
    {
      "factorStandard": "ASME-VV40-2018",
      "factorType": "Use error",
      "type": "CredibilityFactor",
      "requiredLevel": 1,
      "achievedLevel": 1,
      "factorStatus": "assessed",
      "acceptanceCriteria": "Simulation setup reviewed by a second analyst; boundary conditions and material properties checked against source documentation.",
      "rationale": "An independent peer review of the simulation setup was conducted by a senior CFD engineer not involved in the original model construction. Boundary conditions, material properties, turbulence model selection (SST k-ω), and rotating reference frame configuration were verified against the published FDA pump protocol. No use errors were identified. Level 1 is satisfied."
    },
    {
      "factorStandard": "ASME-VV40-2018",
      "factorType": "Model form",
      "type": "CredibilityFactor",
      "requiredLevel": 1,
      "achievedLevel": 1,
      "factorStatus": "not-assessed",
      "acceptanceCriteria": "Not required at MRL 2 for this factor.",
      "rationale": "Model form uncertainty assessment is not required at Model Risk Level 2 for a Class II device with medium model influence. The factor is scoped out per the MRL 2 assessment plan. Level 1 not-assessed is acceptable."
    },
    {
